Red Blood uses a split-license model.

Scope

1. Creative content

Unless a file or directory states otherwise, the repository's creative content is
licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0
International license.

This includes, for example:

- Markdown worldbuilding and story files
- Character sheets and other lore documents
- JSON character data and setting data created as part of the fiction project
- Image and illustrative assets created for the setting

See [LICENSE-CONTENT]

Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International

The creative content in this repository is licensed under the
Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International license
(CC BY-NC-SA 4.0), unless a more specific notice says otherwise.

You are free to:

- Share — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format
- Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the material

Under the following terms:

- Attribution — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the license,
  and indicate if changes were made.
- NonCommercial — You may not use the material for commercial purposes.
- ShareAlike — If you remix, transform, or build upon the material, you must
  distribute your contributions under the same license as the original.
- No additional restrictions — You may not apply legal terms or technological
  measures that legally restrict others from doing anything the license permits.

Official license URL:
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

Full legal code:
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/legalcode

2. Code and tooling

Code, scripts, automation, and tooling files are licensed under the MIT License,
unless a file or directory states otherwise.

This includes, for example:

- Utility scripts
- Local automation
- Tooling and integration code
- Configuration examples that are software-oriented in nature

See [LICENSE-CODE].

